  "What is an 'electromagnetic wave'?": "",
  "A wave consisting of oscillating electric and magnetic fields propagating through space": "",
  "A mechanical wave that requires a physical medium like air or water to propagate": "",
  "A disturbance in the gravitational field caused by accelerating massive objects": "",
  "A sound wave that has been amplified by electrical equipment like loudspeakers": "",
  "An electromagnetic wave consists of oscillating electric and magnetic fields perpendicular to each other and to the direction of travel. It does not need a medium to propagate.": "",
  "What is 'Gauss's Law' for electricity?": "",
  "The total electric flux through a closed surface is proportional to the enclosed charge": "",
  "The total magnetic flux through any closed surface always equals exactly zero": "",
  "A changing magnetic field creates a circulating electric field around it": "",
  "A current-carrying wire produces circular magnetic field lines around itself": "",
  "Gauss's Law (Electric): ∮E·dA = Q/ε₀. The total electric flux through any closed surface equals the enclosed charge divided by ε₀.": "",
  "What is 'Faraday's Law' as one of Maxwell's equations?": "",
  "Electric field lines originate from positive charges and end on negative charges": "",
  "A changing magnetic flux produces a circulating electric field (induced EMF)": "",
  "The total magnetic flux through any closed surface is always equal to zero": "",
  "Magnetic fields are created by electric currents flowing through conductors": "",
  "Faraday's Law (as a Maxwell equation): ∮E·dl = −dΦ_B/dt. A changing magnetic flux induces a circulating electric field, which can drive current in a conductor.": "",
  "What is a 'magnetic monopole'?": "",
