  "A student asks why cutting a magnet in half does not produce isolated north and south poles. Which Maxwell equation explains this?": "",
  "Gauss's Law for Electricity, because charges are conserved in the process": "",
  "Gauss's Law for Magnetism, because magnetic monopoles do not exist": "",
  "Faraday's Law, because cutting induces currents that recreate both poles": "",
  "Ampere's Law, because the internal currents rearrange to form new poles": "",
  "Gauss's Law for Magnetism (∮B·dA = 0) tells us magnetic monopoles do not exist. Cutting a magnet produces two smaller magnets, each with its own north and south pole.": "",
